<br>
As she stepped into the darkness, she cursed her weak barbarian eyesight. She scanned the immediate surroundings as best she could. She was turning to re-enter the bar, intent on taking out her frustration on someone when she noticed a hunched shape in the darkness… <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farbria>Farbria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/04 3:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=832.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chosen Spirit</span><hr size=1> 'Now go and ponish your armor, pupin...she said 'GO AND PONISH YOUR...bleh'.<br>
Sigella sits on her bed in her small chamber, a big pile of bloody and dirty armor stocked up around her. An angry look on her face she keeps muttering to herself: 'Sometimes she makes me crazy, she treats me like I cannot take a step alone..and then that spelling error...'ponish'...'<br>
Sigella almost has to chuckle, and the bad mood vanishes a bit.<br>
It has been a hard day with Farbria the grumpy rogue, who took over her education after she fled Neriak and it was Farbria that guided her into these halls. <br>
They spent a whole day in the gulf of Gunthak, where she was taught the arts to master a hammer, shield and throwing spells at the same time, her teacher watching her flailing away at the undeath and merciless pointing out and correcting her failures. Later the little rogue went to took a beating and let her exercise in the arts to keep someone alive...she took quite a beating but it went quite good, she thought.<br>
As Sigella tossed away the heavy red chestplate, now shiny again and stands up to stretch a bit, she notices a 'thud' from a nearby room. Curious, she puts on a plain black dress over her red underwear, the only belongings she brought along from neriak, and steps outside her chamber.<br>
The corridor is dark and Sigella could not tell from which side the sound came from - the door to the left belongs to her teacher, but she remembers that these hours of the night, Farbria usually sits in some bar, paying reference to her last name -Fassbier-, so she figures to check the other door, Master Echtelions room - a bit shy she knocks on the door.<br>
'Master Echtelion, 'tis Sigella... are you alright in there?'<br>
No answer.<br>
After checking that no one is in the corridor she bends down to peek through the keyhole (( fergive my bad english, not my native tongue)). All she can see is an open window, a big old looking table full of maps and books and parchments... and a naked white foot in bright red slippers behind the table.<br>
'Oh no' - she tries to open the door...but its locked - Trembling, she thinks what to do, then runs off towards the guild halls doors - as she has almost reached the door, it swings open with quite some energy and Farbria stumples in, giggling, carrying 3 or 4 bottles of ale with her, and looking back over her shoulder she starts to speak but swallows the words as she notices Sigella standing next to the door -'Fabria, something terrible has happened to Echtelion - he lies in his room and doesnt -' <br>
Farbria interrupts her with a motion of her hand 'One moment, young one' - then she whispers some words to an unseen person outside the door, shrugs her shoulders and closes the door with a footkick. Putting the bottles down on the floor, she follows Sigella up the stairs, a bit weak in her knees. <br>
<br>
'Can you open the door?', Sigella asks as they arrive in front of Echtelions room.<br>
'Wenn net me see...', Farbria says...and thinks to herself ' I better not tell her that I HAVE opened every door in these halls since I came here...well every door beside the one of Morrigane, I bet she put a disease trap on the lock'.<br>
<br>
However, a simple dagger and a skilled hand is enough to open Echtelions door, Farbria steps in and after a look on the tall high elf on the floor, she turns to Sigella and says 'Hurry, my pupin, go and find Fenuna, and if you see them send Toraka and Areni here too, and Rivervane...now HURRY!'<br>
